27/10/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Parliament is considering whether to use the military in the fight against organised crime, the head of the parliamentary commission for internal security, Nikolay Svinarov, told bTV Thursday (27 October).
He did not elaborate.
Svinarov's statement came a day after a top banker, Emil Kyulev, was shot dead in Sofia in what is seen as the latest in a series of contract murders.
(bTV, Mediapool, Dnevnik - 27/10/05)
